for getting you into college.

97
00:07:46,265 --> 00:07:47,994
I had a hard day at school, I'm tired,

98
00:07:48,100 --> 00:07:50,728
and I'm gonna go relax now
for half an hour.

99
00:07:52,605 --> 00:07:55,073
Then I will do my work. Okay?

100
00:08:04,350 --> 00:08:05,647
HARRIS: George?

101
00:08:08,821 --> 00:08:09,810
The fuck are you doing?

102
00:08:10,656 --> 00:08:12,146
I'm drawing.

103
00:08:12,291 --> 00:08:14,953
Are you sketching your subject,
you little shit?

104
00:08:15,194 --> 00:08:16,627
Yes.

105
00:08:22,468 --> 00:08:25,631
- I don't have a subject, Harris.
- Why the heck not?

106
00:08:26,272 --> 00:08:27,739
I don't know.

107
00:08:27,874 --> 00:08:30,468
George, you're going to have to start
digging around in there,

108
00:08:30,576 --> 00:08:32,601
so you can develop that talent of yours,

109
00:08:32,712 --> 00:08:35,010
so you can start to use that brain of yours

110
00:08:35,114 --> 00:08:37,378
to express that beautiful heart of yours.

111
00:08:38,684 --> 00:08:40,982
So, figure out what you want to say,
and say it.

112
00:08:42,154 --> 00:08:44,145
- Harris.
- Yes.

113
00:08:45,358 --> 00:08:47,087
I don't have anything to say.

114
