an afterthought.

129
00:09:40,880 --> 00:09:42,507
ADD?

130
00:09:42,615 --> 00:09:44,446
No, they tried everything.

131
00:09:44,550 --> 00:09:47,314
Ritalin, Lexapro, tutors, therapy.

132
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:50,218
Nothing worked. I'm the Teflon slacker.

133
00:09:51,257 --> 00:09:55,216
No, it's more like,
we're living in a dying time, you know?

134
00:09:55,328 --> 00:09:59,094
I mean, you got global warming, wars,
terrorism, tsunamis.

135
00:09:59,198 --> 00:10:02,258
- Okay...
- We're definitely on the downhill side.

136
00:10:02,535 --> 00:10:05,299
So, what are we working towards?
What's the point?

137
00:10:05,738 --> 00:10:09,037
I thought I had fears,
but they're pretty run-of-the-mill.

138
00:10:09,141 --> 00:10:11,041
- Pain, death.
- Not me.

139
00:10:11,744 --> 00:10:13,006
I fear life.

140
00:10:13,112 --> 00:10:14,101
(LAUGHS)

141
00:10:17,483 --> 00:10:18,973
Do you have any friends, George?

142
00:10:20,953 --> 00:10:22,944
I'm kind of a misanthrope.

143
00:10:23,956 --> 00:10:25,719
Not a choice, just a fact.

144
00:10:32,365 --> 00:10:33,764
Okay, handsome.

145
00:10:43,409 --> 00:10:45,536
Mom! Jesus!

146
00:10:45,845 --> 00:10:47,278
Hi, banana!

147
00:10:52,018 --> 00:10:53,679
You wanna come up?

148
00:10:56,989 --> 00:10:59,423
I'm sorry about that, chicken.
We had a really late night.

149
00:10:59,525 --> 00:11:02,551
I think we got home right before
you left for school.

150
00:11:05,064 --> 00:11:08,192
Mom, this is my new friend, George.

151
00:11:08,300 --> 00:11:09,665
- Well, George.
- Hello, Mrs. Howe.

152
00:11:09,769 --> 00:11:11,396
- What a genuine pleasure.
- Very nice to...

153
00:11:11,504 --> 00:11:12,596
Sally, do you know
where our stemware went?

